  "original_title": "\u0db4\u0dcf\u0db1\u0dca \u0db8\u0dd2\u0dbd \u0db4\u0dcf \u0dc0\u0dd9\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The price of bread will rise",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "With the emergence of a black market mafia for wheat flour, due to having to buy bread flour at a higher price, a 450 gram loaf of bread has to be sold at 300 rupees, says Mr. NK Jayawardena, president of the All Lanka Bakery Owners' Association.",
        "Mr. Jayawardena also says that a 50 kg bundle of wheat flour which was bought for 3500 rupees has to be bought for 25,000 rupees today.",
        "Mr. Jayawardena says that his association has no objection to buying flour at high prices from the black market and selling a loaf of bread at 300 rupees.",
        "But Mr. Jayawardena also says that his union has not taken a decision to sell bread at 300 rupees."
      ],
